pageContext.description: 2 small, rough knobs on face below slight collar; one remains on reverse. Angle of reverse broken away on loop side of squarish socket. Small knob probably indicates lower end of broken-off loop.
pageContext.patina: Rusty patina on reverse, otherwise worn through to dull grey-green metal.
pageContext.surface: worn but fairly even except for loop side where it is damaged.
pageContext.publications: S.S. Frere & W. Hooper, Surrey Arch.Coll., XLIX, 102, Pl. XII.
